CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 26, 1952, pg. 3, reads: "'Courier Comet' Bids for Derby Title - Rufus Alfred, 15-year-old Clairton school boy, hunches over in his sleek, black and silver racer to show bystanders the driving strategy he will use Saturday afternoon at North Park when he attempts to annex the local Soap Box Derby title and qualify for the big meeting of the wooden racing cars in Akron on Aug. 10. Young Alfred, who built his car at a cost of $7.50, is sponsored in his bid by the Courier and showed his gratitude by naming the racer, 'Courier Comet.' - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Rufus Alfred wearing satin jacket and seated in his "Courier Comet" soapbox derby race car, in interior with linoleum floor
